descp2: {'k-means++', 'random', or ndarray, or a callable}, optional Method for initialization, default to 'k-means++': 'k-means++' : selects initial cluster centers for k-mean clustering in a smart way to speed up convergence. See section Notes in k_init for more details. 'random': choose k observations (rows) at random from data for the initial centroids. If an ndarray is passed, it should be of shape (n_clusters, n_features) and gives the initial centers. If a callable is passed, it should take arguments X, k and and a random state and return an initialization.
